    "created_at": "2018-11-03T10:29:15Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-11-03T10:31:08Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Maybe i've swung too far towards \"Everything is a condition\", but this does seem like a good usecase for them.\r\n\r\nWe could replace the `IVictoryConditionInfo` interface with a `GameMode` trait that lists the metadata (name + condition to grant) for each mode.  The victory condition traits would then implement `ConditionalTrait` and be activated by the conditions granted to the World and Player actors (but may need to go via an ExternalCondition to satisfy the linter... bleh).\r\n\r\nThis would give us:\r\n* The ability to customize AI behaviour for each game mode (#15750 and followups)\r\n* The ability to maps to define their own game modes that mix and match existing logic (e.g. `ConquestVictoryConditions` + additional logic implemented in a Lua script)\r\n* The ability to turn toggle arbitrary other player/world traits: e.g. grant custom prereqs, override crate behaviour, change starting unit options, change factions in the lobby if #3012 is ever finished\r\n\r\nWhat do you think?"
  },
